  "text": "## Grafana Legacy to Unified Alerting Migration Implementation\n\n### Legacy Alerting Engine\n\nThe legacy alerting engine in Grafana is defined in **pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/alert_mig.go**, which creates and manages the following database tables:\n\n1. **alert** - The core legacy alert table containing dashboard-based alerts with fields like dashboard_id, panel_id, name, message, state, settings, frequency, handler, severity, silenced, execution_error, eval_data, eval_date, new_state_date, state_changes, created, and updated.\n\n2. **alert_notification** - Stores legacy alert notification channels (name, type, settings)\n\n3. **alert_rule_tag** - Tags associated with legacy alert rules\n\nThese tables represent the pre-8.0 alert system in Grafana that was dashboard-centric and tied to specific dashboard panels.\n\n### Unified Alerting (ngalert) Storage\n\nThe unified alerting engine is implemented across multiple locations:\n\n#### Core Storage Implementation\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/store/alert_rule.go** (DBstore): Main implementation of the RuleStore interface providing methods like GetAlertRuleByUID, ListAlertRules, ListAlertRulesPaginated, InsertAlertRules, UpdateAlertRules, DeleteAlertRulesByUID, and state management.\n\n- **pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ualert/tables.go**: Defines all unified alerting tables including:\n  - alert_rule: Stores alert rule definitions with UID, OrgID, title, condition, data, labels, annotations, namespace_uid, rule_group, eval_behavior, etc.\n  - alert_rule_version: Tracks version history of alert rules\n  - alert_definition: Stores alert definitions\n  - alert_definition_version: Version tracking for definitions\n  - alert_instance: Tracks current alert instances/states\n  - alert_rule_state: Stores rule state history\n  - alert_configuration: Stores alertmanager configurations\n  - alert_configuration_history: Tracks configuration versions\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/store/alertmanager.go**: Handles alertmanager-specific storage\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/models/alert_rule.go**: Defines the AlertRule, AlertRuleKey, and related model types used throughout the unified alerting system\n\n#### Legacy Storage Wrappers for Backward Compatibility\n\nThe system maintains backward compatibility through legacy storage implementations:\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/config.go**: Stores and manages alertmanager configurations for backward compatibility\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/compat.go**: Contains conversion functions like InhibitRuleToInhibitionRule for converting legacy format to unified format\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/imported.go**: Handles imported legacy configurations (especially from Prometheus/external sources) with the ImportedConfigRevision structure managing merged rules, routes, and receivers\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/routes.go**: Manages legacy routing tree definitions\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/receivers.go**: Handles legacy receiver (notification channel) definitions\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/inhibition_rules.go**: Manages inhibition rules with backward compatibility\n\n- **pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/persist.go**: Defines storage interface for persisting legacy alertmanager configs\n\n#### Registry Apps Storage Layers\n\n- **pkg/registry/apps/alerting/rules/alertrule/legacy_storage.go**: Provides legacy storage wrapper for alert rules (type legacyStorage)\n\n- **pkg/registry/apps/alerting/rules/recordingrule/legacy_storage.go**: Provides legacy storage wrapper for recording rules\n\n- **pkg/registry/apps/alerting/notifications/receiver/legacy_storage.go**: Legacy storage for notification receivers\n\n- **pkg/registry/apps/alerting/notifications/routingtree/legacy_storage.go**: Legacy storage for routing trees\n\n### Migration and Conversion Scripts\n\n#### Main Migration Engine\n\n**pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ualert/ualert.go**: The core migration that executes the upgrade from legacy alerting to unified alerting. The upgradeNgAlerting type implements CodeMigration interface and:\n\n1. Updates alert configurations from legacy format\n2. Migrates alertmanager configuration files\n3. Handles organization assignment for configurations\n4. Includes FixEarlyMigration for handling configurations created before version 8.2 with org_id=0\n\n**pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ualert/tables.go**: Defines all database table migrations for the unified alerting system, including the AddTablesMigrations function that sets up alert_rule, alert_rule_version, and related tables.\n\n#### Prometheus/Alertmanager Conversion\n\n**pkg/services/ngalert/api/api_convert_prometheus.go**: Implements ConvertPrometheusSrv service for converting Prometheus-compatible alerting rules to Grafana format:\n\n1. **RouteConvertPrometheusGetRules**: Returns all Grafana-managed alert rules imported from Prometheus sources\n2. **RouteConvertPrometheusGetAlertmanagerConfig**: Retrieves imported Alertmanager configurations\n3. **NewConvertPrometheusSrv**: Initializes the conversion service with rule store, datasource cache, and alert rule service\n\nThis service enables importing rules from Mimir and other Prometheus-compatible systems while preserving the original rule definitions for round-trip compatibility.\n\n**pkg/services/ngalert/api/prometheus_conversion.go**: Handler wrapper for the conversion API endpoints\n\n#### Compatibility Layer\n\n**pkg/services/ngalert/store/compat.go**: Provides compatibility functions for converting between legacy and new formats:\n- convertAlertRuleToModel: Converts alertRule database objects to ngalert models.AlertRule\n- AlertRuleConvertOptions: Controls which fields to parse during conversion\n\n#### Provisioning API\n\n**pkg/services/ngalert/provisioning/alert_rules.go**: Implements AlertRuleService for rule provisioning:\n- Manages rule CRUD operations\n- Handles rule group operations\n- Manages provenance (who created/modified rules)\n- Enforces access control\n- Validates rule groups and quotas\n- Integrates with folder service for namespace management\n\n**pkg/services/ngalert/api/api_provisioning.go**: Provisioning API implementation using AlertRuleService\n\n### Migration Flow\n\nThe migration path from legacy to unified alerting:\n\n1. **Legacy System** (dashboard alerts in alert table)\n   ↓\n2. **Migration Code** (upgradeNgAlerting migration)\n   ↓\n3. **Unified Storage** (alert_rule table and related tables)\n   ↓\n4. **Provisioning API** (AlertRuleService)\n   ↓\n5. **Conversion API** (ConvertPrometheusSrv for Prometheus imports)\n\nThe legacy storage wrapper classes maintain backward compatibility by wrapping the unified storage while converting between legacy and new formats on-the-fly, allowing existing code and external tools (like mimirtool) to continue working with the familiar Prometheus format.\n"
